# API Routes — Fast Response (No Waterfalls)

Sequential `await` calls add full round-trip latency each time. Parallelize independent work so the route returns quickly.

## Do: Start then await

Start all independent operations immediately, then await together.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — config and data are sequential
export async function GET(request: Request) {
  const session = await auth();
  const config = await fetchConfig();
  const data = await fetchData(session.user.id);
  return Response.json({ data, config });
}

// ✅ GOOD — auth needed for data; config is independent
export async function GET(request: Request) {
  const sessionPromise = auth();
  const configPromise = fetchConfig();
  const session = await sessionPromise;
  const [config, data] = await Promise.all([
    configPromise,
    fetchData(session.user.id),
  ]);
  return Response.json({ data, config });
}
```

## Do: Defer await until the branch that needs it

If one path does not need a value, do not await it before branching.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
const user = await fetchUser();
if (skipDetail) return Response.json({ skipped: true });
const detail = await fetchDetail(user.id);

// ✅ GOOD
if (skipDetail) return Response.json({ skipped: true });
const user = await fetchUser();
const detail = await fetchDetail(user.id);
```

## Do: Promise.all for fully independent fetches

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — 3 round trips in sequence
const categories = await getCategories();
const products = await getProducts();
const options = await getOptions();

// ✅ GOOD — 1 round trip
const [categories, products, options] = await Promise.all([
  getCategories(),
  getProducts(),
  getOptions(),
]);
```

Keep cache headers for routes that set them (e.g. reference data: long s-maxage; products: shorter TTL). See `next.config.mjs` `headers()`.
